    "biography": "<p>A stone-skinned winged gargoyle (Gargoyle saxsexus) that perches on tall derelict buildings. More dangerous the more it is injured.</p><p><strong>Powers:</strong> Concealment (Personal), Enhanced Physical Attributes (Strength, 1×/day for [Essence]D6 Combat Turns), Hardened Armor, Noxious Breath</p><p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Allergy (Sunlight, Nuisance), Vulnerability (Iron)</p><p><em>Attacks: 11S. Habitat: Tall buildings, usually derelict. Range: Rare throughout Europe; more common in Tir Nan Og and urban Germany. Flying Quickness multiplier is 4. 2D6 Initiative dice. Book Body 10/7 (Hardened Armor 7), Intelligence 2/5. PAE p.41.</em></p>",
